- The `flare_class_confidence` is a measure of the reliability of the flare class assignment.

- "Prediction errors" refer to the absolute difference between the predicted and actual times of solar events;
- "Rank" is determined by ordering these errors, with lower ranks indicating smaller errors;
- "Solar flares" are a type of solar event characterized by sudden increases in solar radiation.

